info.orestes.rest

Class RestServlet

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.servlet.GenericServlet
      • info.orestes.rest.RestServlet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, javax.servlet.Servlet, javax.servlet.ServletConfig

    public abstract class RestServlet
extends javax.servlet.GenericServlet
    An RestServlet represents a resource or a group of resources which is selected by the RestRouter its entities are converted by the ConversionHandler and is dispatched by the RestServletHandler .

    Concurrency Note: One instance can be used by multiple threads at the same time. So shared state access must by synchronized accurately.
